charles vii (6 august 1697 â€“ 20 january 1745) was the prince-elector of bavaria from 1726 and holy roman emperor from 24 january 1742 until his death, in 1745. a member of the house of wittelsbach, charles was notably the only person not born of the house of habsburg to become emperor in over three centuries (although he was descended from the habsburg philip i of castile by 27 different ways).